<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10184356>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Dactylolabis (Dactylolabis) longicauda Alexander, 1922. A. habitus with darker coloration, lateral view; B. same with lighter coloration; C. wing; D. hypopygium, dorsal view; E. male hypandrium, ventral view; F. lateral lobe of proctiger, outer view; G. gonocoxite, outer surface; H. gonostyli, dorsal surface. I. aedeagal complex, dorsal view. J. same, lateral view (left side directing dorsally). Scale bars: A–B, 3 mm; D–J, 0.1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10184356/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10184358>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Ovipositor of Dactylolabis (Dactylolabis) longicauda Alexander, 1922. A. ovipositor, lateral view; B. cercus, lateral view; C. sternite 9 ventral view (upper side directing posteriorly); D. sternite 8 and hypogynial valve, ventral view; E. genital frame, dorsal view (upper side directing posteriorly); G. same, lateral surface (left side directing dorsally). Scale bars: A–G, 0.1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10184358/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10184360>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Distributions of Japanese species of Dactylolabis. A. D. (D.) diluta (red circle) and D. (D.) kyororo sp. nov. (green square); B. D. (D.) longicauda." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10184360/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

